<tmc-service-inc>
<pub id="RM0251U">
<servcat id="35">
<name>SUSPENSION &amp; AXLE</name>
<section id="1000J_S000X" variety="S000X">
<name>TIRE AND WHEEL</name>
<ttl id="1000J_S000X_738JZ_T00GU" variety="T00GU">
<name>TIRE PRESSURE WARNING SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM000000XN7008X" category="C" type-id="304MI" name-id="TW0DI-03" from="200601">
<dtccode>C2165/65</dtccode>
<dtcname>Abnormal Temperature Inside ID1 Tire</dtcname>
<dtccode>C2166/66</dtccode>
<dtcname>Abnormal Temperature Inside ID2 Tire</dtcname>
<dtccode>C2167/67</dtccode>
<dtcname>Abnormal Temperature Inside ID3 Tire</dtcname>
<dtccode>C2168/68</dtccode>
<dtcname>Abnormal Temperature Inside ID4 Tire</dtcname>
<dtccode>C2169/69</dtccode>
<dtcname>Abnormal Temperature Inside ID5 Tire</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000XN7008X_02" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HK00001">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>Each tire pressure warning valve and transmitter measures the internal temperature of its tire as well as tire pressure, and transmits the information to the tire pressure warning ECU along with the transmitter ID. If the measured temperature is out of the specified range, the tire pressure warning ECU recognizes it as a malfunction, outputs DTCs, and comes on the tire pressure warning light after blinking for 1 minute.</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.27in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.90in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="2.91in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC Detecting Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>C2165/65</ptxt>
<ptxt>C2166/66</ptxt>
<ptxt>C2167/67</ptxt>
<ptxt>C2168/68</ptxt>
<ptxt>C2169/69</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Temperature inside the tire exceeds 119°C (246.2°F) more than once.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Tires</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Tire pressure warning valve and transmitter</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Tire pressure warning ECU</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>It is necessary to perform the procedure to identify the tire pressure warning valve and transmitter that is malfunctioning because it cannot be identified by the output DTC.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>DTC 2169/69 is used only when the vehicle is equipped with full-size spare tire.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XN7008X_03" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HL00001">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>When replacing the tire pressure warning ECU, read the IDs stored in the ECU using the intelligent tester and note them down before removal.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>It is necessary to perform initialization (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XMZ008X"/>) after registration (See page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000XN1008X"/>) of the transmitter IDs into the tire pressure warning ECU after the ECU and/or valve and transmitter has been replaced.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten3>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Set the tire pressure to the specified value.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000XN7008X_04" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0003" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HM00001">
<testtitle>CHECK TIRES</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the tire is not flat, and there is no indication of air pressure drop.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Tire is normal.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If a tire is damaged, the tire pressure warning valve and transmitter may also have been damaged at the same time.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0008" fin="false">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0024" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0008" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HN00001">
<testtitle>IDENTIFY TRANSMITTER CORRESPONDING TO DTC</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Set the tire pressure to the specified value.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Cold tire inflation pressure</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Tire size</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Front kPa (kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Rear kPa (kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>P215/60R16 94W</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>210 (2.1, 31) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>210 (2.1, 31) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>P215/55R17 93V</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>220 (2.2, 32) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>220 (2.2, 32) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<ptxt>*1: For driving under 100 mph (160 km/h)</ptxt>
<ptxt>*2: For driving at 100 mph (160 km/h) or over</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Display the "TIREPRESS" data for each wheel using the intelligent tester.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Rapidly reduce the tire pressure for each wheel at least 40 kPa (0.41 kg/cm<sup>2</sup>, 5.8 psi) within 30 seconds.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the DATA LIST</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="4">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.12in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL4" colwidth="1.42in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Measurement Item/Display</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Normal Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Diagnostic Note</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TIREPRESS1</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>ID1 tire inflation pressure/</ptxt>
<ptxt>min.: 0 kPa (0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 0 psi), max.: 637.5 kPa (6.48 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 92.2 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Actual tire inflation pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>-</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TIREPRESS2</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>ID2 tire inflation pressure/</ptxt>
<ptxt>min.: 0 kPa (0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 0 psi), max.: 637.5 kPa (6.48 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 92.2 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Actual tire inflation pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>-</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TIREPRESS3</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>ID3 tire inflation pressure/</ptxt>
<ptxt>min.: 0 kPa (0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 0 psi), max.: 637.5 kPa (6.48 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 92.2 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Actual tire inflation pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>-</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TIREPRESS4</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>ID4 tire inflation pressure/</ptxt>
<ptxt>min.: 0 kPa (0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 0 psi), max.: 637.5 kPa (6.48 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 92.2 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Actual tire inflation pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>-</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TIREPRESS5</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>ID5 tire inflation pressure/</ptxt>
<ptxt>min.: 0 kPa (0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 0 psi), max.: 637.5 kPa (6.48 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 92.2 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Actual tire inflation pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>-</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</test1>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Detection Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>One of "TIREPRESS" data (ID1 to ID4 or ID5) changed.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Normal</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>No "TIREPRESS" data changed.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Transmitter corresponding to DTC</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<atten3>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>It takes about 1 minute or more to display the updated data.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>When no "TIREPRESS" data has changed, reset the tire pressure to the appropriate specified value and rotate the tire 90 to 270 degrees. Then forcibly transmit the transmitter ID and recheck it.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Record the transmitter ID and position that is normal condition.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten3>
<test1>
<ptxt>When the "TIREPRESS" data (ID1 to ID4 or ID5) has changed, repeat this procedure to identify the tire pressure warning valve and transmitter that corresponds to a DTC.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>When all of the "TIREPRESS" data (ID1 to ID4 or ID5) has changed, identify the malfunctioning tire pressure warning valve and transmitter based on the recorded ID numbers and output DTC.</ptxt>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0009" fin="false">NEXT</down>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0009" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HO00001">
<testtitle>REPLACE TIRE PRESSURE WARNING VALVE AND TRANSMITTER</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Replace the identified tire pressure warning valve and transmitter with a new one.</ptxt>
</test1>
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Before installing a new tire pressure warning valve and transmitter, read and write down its transmitter ID.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>The IDs for the tire pressure warning valve and transmitter not be replaced should be checked using tester and recorded.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0020" fin="false">NEXT</down>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0020" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HP00001">
<testtitle>CHECK REGISTRATION OF TRANSMITTER ID</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Register the transmitter ID for 4 or 5 wheels (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XN1008X"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Set the tire pressure of all wheels to the specified value.</ptxt>
</test1>
<spec>
<title>Cold tire inflation pressure</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="2.36in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Tire size</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Front kPa (kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Rear kPa (kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>P215/60R16 94W</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>210 (2.1, 31) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>210 (2.1, 31) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>P215/55R17 93V</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>220 (2.2, 32) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>220 (2.2, 32) <sup>*1</sup> 240 (2.4, 35)<sup>*2</sup>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<ptxt>*1: For driving under 100 mph (160 km/h)</ptxt>
<ptxt>*2: For driving at 100 mph (160 km/h) or over</ptxt>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0021" fin="false">NEXT</down>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0021" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HQ00001">
<testtitle>PERFORM INITIALIZATION</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Perform initialization (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XMZ008X"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0023" fin="false">NEXT</down>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0023" proc-id="RM0250U___00005HR00001">
<testtitle>CHECK DTC</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Check for a DTC (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XMZ008X"/>).</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Any of the DTCs from C2165/65 to C2168/68 or C2169/69 are output.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Any of the DTCs from C2165/65 to C2168/68 or C2169/69 are not output.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>B</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0022" fin="true">A</down>
<right ref="RM000000XN7008X_04_0014" fin="true">B</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0014">
<testtitle>END</testtitle>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0024">
<testtitle>REPLACE TIRE AND TIRE PRESSURE WARNING VALVE AND TRANSMITTER</testtitle>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000XN7008X_04_0022">
<testtitle>REPLACE TIRE PRESSURE WARNING ECU</testtitle>
</testgrp>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
